com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Class CollectionOrder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.CollectionOrder

  • public class CollectionOrder
extends java.lang.Object
    The CollectionOrder class provides methods for determining the sorting order of a collection. That is, given a collection with a well defined iteration order, and a Comparable implementation on its contents, this class's methods will return the order in which the collection's contents should be accessed to be correctly sorted.

        public static <T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>> int[] getOrder(java.lang.Iterable<T> collection)
        Get the sorted order for a specified iterable collection, using the default Comparable implementation. The returned array will list the (0-based) index order of the sorted elements in the collection.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type held by the collection.
        Parameters:
        collection - The iterable collection.
        Returns:
        an array specifying the sorted order of collection.

      • getOrder

        public static <T> int[] getOrder(java.lang.Iterable<T> collection,
                 SetList<T> reference)
        Get the sorted order for a specified iterable collection, using a reference setlist to define the ordering relationships. The returned array will list the (0-based) index order of the sorted elements in the collection.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type held by the collection.
        Parameters:
        collection - The iterable collection.
        reference - The reference setlist. The order of the elements in this setlist will define the sorting for the collection.
        Returns:
        an array specifying the sorted order of collection using reference to define the ordering.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any element in collection is not found in reference, or if the size of collection is not the same as reference. //todo: relax this latter restriction
